---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Oman Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/oman/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
  { title: 'Bahrain for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bahrain' },
  { title: 'Qatar for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/qatar' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'omanFit', header: 'Oman Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'OMR 145-205/mo', omanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'OMR 170-245/mo', omanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'OMR 135-190/mo', omanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'OMR 125-175/mo', omanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Oman Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: 'OMR 40-100/mo', omanFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'OMR 135-205', annual: 'OMR 1,620-2,460' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'OMR 185-280', annual: 'OMR 2,220-3,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'OMR 250-375', annual: 'OMR 3,000-4,500' },
  { category: 'Oman Public Healthcare', monthly: 'Subsidized', annual: 'Small fees' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'OMR 15-40/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Oman 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Oman. Dramatic landscapes, traditional Arabian culture, good healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Oman"
  subheadline="Oman offers authentic Arabian culture, stunning landscapes from mountains to coastline, and new retirement residence pathways—the Gulf's most traditional destination."
  heroImage="/images/countries/oman-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Oman</h2>
  <p>
    Oman is the Gulf's most authentic destination—traditional Arabian culture, dramatic mountains and wadis, pristine coastline, and genuine hospitality. Less flashy than Dubai but more characterful. The Investor Residence Visa provides pathway for retirees with income or property.
  </p>

  <p>
    Muscat offers capital living with traditional architecture and modern amenities. Salalah in the south has monsoon greenery unique to the region. Nizwa provides mountain heritage. The coastal areas offer beaches without overdevelopment. Oman feels different from its neighbors.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good; modern private facilities in Muscat</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> OMR 800-1,500/month (~$2,100-3,900); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Hot summers; Salalah has monsoon season</li>
      <li><strong>Tax:</strong> No income tax; minimal other taxes</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Traditional, authentic, hospitable</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Oman's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Oman has good healthcare—Royal Hospital and Sultan Qaboos University Hospital lead the public sector. Private hospitals like Muscat Private Hospital, Starcare Hospital, and Apollo provide quality care. Standards in Muscat are good; other areas are more limited.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is subsidized for residents (small fees apply). Expats typically use private facilities with insurance. For complex cases, Dubai (1 hour flight) is accessible. Oman is implementing mandatory health insurance—international coverage is increasingly important.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Mandatory Insurance Coming</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Oman is implementing mandatory health insurance for all residents. International insurance from major providers typically meets requirements. Ensure your coverage is recognized—this is becoming essential for residence permits and healthcare access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Oman offers improving options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Investor Residence Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Property investment of OMR 50,000+ (~$130,000) in approved developments grants 5-year renewable residence. For retirees with investment capacity, this provides stable long-term pathway.
  </p>

  <h3>Income-Based Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Demonstrating sufficient income (typically OMR 1,000+/month from pension or investments) can support residence applications. Combined with property ownership, strengthens application.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For testing the waters—10-year multiple entry visa available for some nationalities. Allows extended stays without full residence, useful for snowbirds or those exploring Oman.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Oman:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mandatory:</strong> Health insurance increasingly required for residence</li>
    <li><strong>Investor Visa:</strong> Insurance typically required for application</li>
    <li><strong>Coverage level:</strong> Must meet Omani regulatory standards</li>
    <li><strong>International:</strong> Major providers generally accepted</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Oman</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is recommended—local Omani insurers often have age restrictions. Cigna, BUPA, and Allianz are recognized and typically meet requirements. Include Dubai coverage for specialized care. Muscat's private healthcare handles most needs well.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Oman, international providers work best:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Oman</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Gulf network, recognized in Oman</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Middle East focus, regional expertise</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Gulf pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers recognized for Oman residence.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Oman are moderate for the Gulf region:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Omani private care is affordable; high deductible for major needs</li>
    <li><strong>Gulf-only coverage:</strong> Excluding Europe/US reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations OMR 15-25; easy cash</li>
    <li><strong>Dubai access:</strong> Include UAE for complex care options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Nature Lover, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Buying OMR 75,000 property near Muscat. £2,000/month pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Investor Residence Visa. Cigna Global with UK coverage. Uses Muscat Private Hospital.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~OMR 170/month (~£360). Mountain/coastal lifestyle; authentic Arabia.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: American Couple, Both 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension $4,500/month. Seeking authentic Gulf experience.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Property purchase + income proof. BUPA Global for both. Dubai access for complex care.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~OMR 450/month combined (~$1,170). Traditional Arabia with modern comforts.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Indian Professional, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Former Oman worker returning. Pension + savings. Familiar with country.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Income-based residence. Now Health regional coverage. Uses Apollo Oman.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Now Health ~OMR 140/month (~$365). Known environment; established networks.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How traditional is Oman?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        More traditional than UAE or Bahrain but welcoming. Omani culture is proud and distinctive—dishdasha and traditional dress common. Alcohol available at hotels. Modest dress expected in public. Society is conservative but hospitable. Genuine Arabian experience without strict limitations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What makes Oman different from other Gulf states?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Authenticity—Oman never became as flashy as Dubai. Mountains, wadis, coastline provide dramatic landscapes. Culture is preserved not performed. Slower pace. Less construction chaos. Genuine hospitality. For those seeking Gulf living with character rather than glitz, Oman delivers.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's Salalah like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Unique in the Gulf—monsoon (khareef) season June-September brings green landscapes and cool temperatures when rest of Gulf is unbearable. Popular escape from summer heat. Rest of year is dry and warm. Different climate and character from Muscat. Growing for retirees.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Oman healthcare adequate for seniors?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Good in Muscat—private hospitals handle most senior needs. Complex cardiac, oncology, or specialized care may need Dubai (1 hour flight). Public hospitals are decent. Overall adequate for comfortable retirement with international insurance backup for complex needs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers recognized for Oman Investor Residence.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Omani authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
